#- §lNegotiations with Wesbury§r

Leader of the young Admiralty of Wesbury Orinnari publicly considered on the 16th of March 2021 creating an “Open Pursuit” treaty between Mount September and his country, saying
"the fundamental
#- premise of the extradition treaty was that signatories would refrain from claiming jurisdiction over captured persons if the claim of jurisdiction is based solely on location”.
However, when it was pointed out that Orinnari could simply
go through MtS's simple extradition
#- processs, the conversation quickly turned into an argument, as the leader of Wesbury thought it was wrong that he would have to “beg” to keep the pearl, saying “I need to explain and beg and justify me wanting to pearl them”, also stating it was unfair that other nations
#- could impose themselves on crimes done to other nations simply because they possessed the pearl. The argument saw a back and forth of presenting similar arguments over and over again for a long time, as both sides refused to concede.
Orinnari later stated
"The Admiralty of
#- Wesbury has formally withdrawn from treaty negotiations with Mouth September since the Lord Admiral currently considers Mount September as an unreliable neighbour.”
The Lord Admiral of Wesbury then, on the 23rd, proposed another solution:
an embassy; but not 
#- just any embassy, a “condominium” that would act as “a secure storage building where [Wesbury would] put captured persons until extradition is allowed”.
A location was proposed in the newly created embassy channel for Wesbury:
a small island that is
#- roughly equally close to Wesbury then to Mount September.
Orinnari said that he did not want two embassies in the two countries, one for each other, because
"Wesbury would have to design and construct an aesthetic build with a secure storage room because the 
#- likelihood of someone committing a crime in Wesbury and fleeing to Mount September's borders is so much greater than the reverse”, also stating that it would take up the limited space in Wesbury.
Since this solution is a little complex, it was 
also proposed that
Mount September 
#- simply annex the island and Wesbury can build an embassy as private property, or that they can simply build in an already existing claim in MtS.
However, Wesbury would want to keep the embassy “at arms reach”, and when an alternative closer island was already
#- within the claims of MtS was proposed, it was refused due to it being a beach biome and that other people may want to use it for farms or attempt to illegally make a farm upon it.
Needless to say, negotiations with the Admiralty of Wesbury are quite tumultuous, we hope they go well.
#- §oWhile this article tries to be unbiased, Mount September was one part of the negotiations and thus cannot be free of bias in this case. For information coming from the other side, please read: §5https://wesbury.netlify.app/news/2021-03-18-treaty-breakdown/
#- §lSmall News§r

§nMeme bills out of control in MtS:

§0Ever since the arrival of a few particularly memish newfriends, who will stay unnamed, meme bills had skyrocketed in MtS, with meme bill after meme bill and the
occasional bill
#- that would invalidate the previous meme bills, the #bills channel was chaotic.
However, on the 24th of March 2021, an old channel initially created in April of 2020 was brought back, known as §9§o#meme-bills§r. In the channel people are free to post their
funny joke bills 
#- without making the Judges who have to count the bills suffer!
Additionally, all of the channel’s messages are archived, just like all other law channels, giving it an air of legitimacy. We welcome this developpement, as now the §9§o#bills§r channel will not be so chaotic and cluttered.

#- §nThraldrek resigns as diplomat:§r

Coming as a shock to all Septembrian, long-time diplomat Thraldrek has resigned, stating “I’m unable to dedicate the time (I think is) necessary to the position. I wish the next Diplomat the best of luck.”
#- Thraldrek was praised as a Diplomat for his skill and experience, notably signing the Christmas Agreement among other accomplishments.
The next person to fill the position would  have to be most likely a willing long standing civ player with a good knowledge of civ
politics and time to 

#- dedicate to it, a combination of attributes not so easy to find. For this reason, Godomasta stated that a new diplomat would most likely not be appointed unless there is an extreme need for one.

#- §nOko, Leader of Anyakova, quits civ:§r

On the 24th of March 2021, Oko, Queen of Kings and Empress of Anykova, made a post on r/civclassics titled “goodnight”, in it was written "think the big night is tonight, last time im using a computer sorry if i fucked you over i
#- never really tried to. keep my legacy and sorry for wasting your time”.
This quitting post came after a debacle in which Oko announced that the evidence which had confirmed 
minemaster’s accusations of having stolen 48 diamond blocks was by Kayla,
former leader of
#- Cascadia. Kayla countered by saying that Oko was throwing a “hissy fit”, stating that she strongly advised against the faking of evidence as well as denouncing Oko for a host of other things.
Kayla's response was followed by Oko’s aforementioned quitting post.

#- We wish Oko well.


§nRaider pearled trying to steal a beacon in Mount September:§r

On the 28th of March 2021, a discord user by the name of Matthew123 from the Commonwealth joined the Mount September
discord and 
#- announced a raider was currently stealing a beacon in MtS. The raider, named SirFrenchie, was promptly pearled by squareblob.
After those events, Frenchie was extradited to the CSA. He was charged with one week of exile pearl, however he was released after one
#- day due to leniency on the part of the CSA. This must have been hard for the Premier of the CSA SandFalls who said “i wanted to adopt him”.
Matthew123 then made a reddit post in which he claimed that TKON / IMC were back, talking about a group of which Frenchie is supposedly a part of,
#- and that they were preparing a full scale invasion of Mount September as well as building a secret vault.
While these claims are over-the-top, it is unknown if they are true; for the sake of MtS, we hope not
